          "code": "RENDER_SUMMARY",
          "id": "1777453613645",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "1777453613646_1",
              "name": "prompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": "You are an intelligent financial close analyst.\n\n**Input Data:**\nAppContext: {{$context.$nodes.PARSE_APP_CONTEXT.$output.result}}\nAccountExceptions: {{$context.$nodes.FETCH_ACCOUNTING_EXCEPTIONS.$output.output}}\nPeriodStatus: {{$context.$nodes.FETCH_PERIOD_STATUS.$output.output}}\nControlsandCompliance: {{$context.$nodes.FETCH_CONTROLS_AND_COMPLIANCE.$output.output}}\nVarianceAnalysis: {{$context.$nodes.FETCH_VARIANCE_ANALYSIS_INFORMATION.$output.output}}\nClearingAccountBalance: {{$context.$nodes.FETCH_CLEARING_ACCOUNT_BALANCE_ANALYSIS.$output.output}}\n\n**Currency Rules**\n- Prefix the formatted amount with the `Currency symbol` \n- `Currency symbol` is derived from AppContext.currencyCode.(for example: $, ₹, €, £ instead of USD, INR, EUR, GBP).\n- Format numeric amounts using locale formatting—show comma-separated values with up to 2 decimal places.\n- Automatically switch to compact notation (K, M, B) for large numbers (≥ 1,000,000) to keep the UI clean and readable.\n\n**Instructions**\n\nGiven section-wise operational data (such as Accounting Exceptions, Period Status, Controls & Compliance, Clearing Account Balance, Variance Analysis), generate a concise executive summary that delivers insights, not descriptions.\n\n**Prompt Guidelines:**\nA more factual and data-driven style for executive summaries should:\n- State observed facts directly\n- Avoid emotional or speculative language\n- Avoid inferred intent or hypothetical outcomes unless explicitly supported by data\n- Focus on metrics, trends, thresholds, and required actions\n- Use neutral wording such as “requires review,” “exceeds threshold,” “remains open,”\nor “increased/decreased”\n\n**Output requirements**\n- generate a one line header in bold text with a maximum of 10 words Eg. <h5>header text</h5>\n- generate summary in bulleted points\n- Maximum 2-3 points\n- each bulleted point should be in maximum of 10-15 words\n- Each bulleted line must be Strictly under 90 characters.\n- Add a breakline at the end of list.\n- Use natural, professional business language (CFO/Controller level)\n- Include key metrics (counts, notable concentrations, comparisons)\n- highlight any amounts, percentages, counts in the summary\n- Follow `Currency Rules` guidelines when using financial figures.\n- Header and Bullet List Must Not Inlcude `$AppContext.ledgerName`, `$AppContext.PeriodName`."
            }
          ],
          "type": "LLM",
          "diagram": {
            "x": 6025,
            "y": 6370
